- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition and language models. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a cache mechanism to speed up decoding, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with personalized language models, which can be seen as a form of personalization in social networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with improving the efficiency of decoding, which is a key component of information retrieval systems.
